---
import BaseHead from '../../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE, SITE_DESCRIPTION } from '../../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={`Documentation - ${SITE_TITLE}`} description="Documentation for OpenVoice AI agents." />
		<style>
			main {
				width: 100%;
				max-width: 1200px;
				margin: 0 auto;
				padding: 2rem;
				font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, sans-serif;
				display: flex;
				gap: 3rem;
				text-align: left;
			}
			.sidebar {
				width: 250px;
				flex-shrink: 0;
				border-right: 1px solid #eaeaea;
				padding-right: 2rem;
				display: none;
				text-align: left;
			}
			@media (min-width: 768px) {
				.sidebar {
					display: block;
				}
			}
			.sidebar h3 {
				font-size: 0.85rem;
				text-transform: uppercase;
				color: #888;
				letter-spacing: 1px;
				margin-bottom: 1rem;
				margin-top: 2rem;
			}
			.sidebar h3:first-child {
				margin-top: 0;
			}
			.sidebar ul {
				list-style: none;
				padding: 0;
				margin: 0;
			}
			.sidebar li {
				margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
			}
			.sidebar a {
				color: #444;
				text-decoration: none;
				font-size: 0.95rem;
				transition: color 0.2s;
			}
			.sidebar a:hover, .sidebar a.active {
				color: #000;
				font-weight: 600;
			}
			.content {
				flex-grow: 1;
				max-width: 800px;
			}
			.content h1 {
				font-size: 2.5rem;
				font-weight: 800;
				margin-bottom: 1rem;
				color: #111;
			}
			.content h2 {
				font-size: 1.75rem;
				font-weight: 700;
				margin-top: 3rem;
				margin-bottom: 1rem;
				color: #111;
			}
			.content h3 {
				font-size: 1.25rem;
				font-weight: 600;
				margin-top: 2rem;
				margin-bottom: 1rem;
				color: #222;
			}
			.content p {
				font-size: 1.1rem;
				line-height: 1.7;
				color: #444;
				margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
			}
			.content ul {
				margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
				padding-left: 1.5rem;
			}
			.content li {
				font-size: 1.1rem;
				line-height: 1.6;
				color: #444;
				margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
			}
			.code-block {
				background: #111;
				color: #fff;
				padding: 1.5rem;
				border-radius: 8px;
				font-family: ui-monospace, Menlo, Monaco, 'Cascadia Mono', 'Segoe UI Mono', 'Roboto Mono', 'Oxygen Mono', 'Ubuntu Monospace', 'Source Code Pro', 'Fira Mono', 'Droid Sans Mono', 'Courier New', monospace;
				font-size: 0.95rem;
				overflow-x: auto;
				margin-bottom: 2rem;
			}
			.callout {
				background: #f8f9fa;
				border-left: 4px solid #000;
				padding: 1.5rem;
				border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0;
				margin-bottom: 2rem;
			}
			.callout p:last-child {
				margin-bottom: 0;
			}
			.callout strong {
				display: block;
				margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
				color: #000;
			}
		</style>
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<aside class="sidebar">
				<h3>Getting Started</h3>
				<ul>
					<li><a href="/docs/introduction" class="active">Introduction</a></li>
					<li><a href="#">Quickstart</a></li>
					<li><a href="#">Self-Hosting</a></li>
					<li><a href="#">Authentication</a></li>
				</ul>

				<h3>Core Concepts</h3>
				<ul>
					<li><a href="#">Agents</a></li>
					<li><a href="#">Models & Integrations</a></li>
					<li><a href="#">Tools & Webhooks</a></li>
					<li><a href="#">Prompts</a></li>
				</ul>

				<h3>API Reference</h3>
				<ul>
					<li><a href="#">Initiate Call</a></li>
					<li><a href="#">Get Call Logs</a></li>
					<li><a href="#">Manage Agents</a></li>
				</ul>
			</aside>

			<section class="content">
				<h1>Introduction</h1>
				<p>Welcome to the official documentation for OpenVoice AI. OpenVoice is a comprehensive, open-source platform for building, simulating, and deploying conversational AI voice agents directly into your existing infrastructure.</p>

				<div class="callout">
					<strong>Open Source First</strong>
					<p>OpenVoice is completely open-source and built for developers. You can run the entire stack on your own AWS, GCP, or local bare-metal hardware without vendor lock-in.</p>
				</div>

				<h2>What can you build?</h2>
				<p>OpenVoice provides the core telephony, real-time streaming, and LLM orchestration required to create interactive, human-like voice agents. Our users typically build:</p>
				<ul>
					<li><strong>Inbound Customer Support:</strong> AI agents that replace traditional IVR menus and answer complex queries via RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation).</li>
					<li><strong>Outbound Campaigns:</strong> Automated cart-recovery or feedback survey bots that can be orchestrated at scale.</li>
					<li><strong>Internal tooling:</strong> Voice interfaces to query your internal databases or trigger workflows via integrations like n8n or Zapier.</li>
				</ul>

				<h2>Architecture Overview</h2>
				<p>Under the hood, OpenVoice is composed of three massive components working synchronously with ultra-low latency:</p>
				<ol>
					<li><strong>Telephony Gateway:</strong> Manages SIP/WebRTC connections (easily attach Twilio, Plivo, or your SIP trunks).</li>
					<li><strong>Speech Engine (ASR & TTS):</strong> Converts user audio to text and synthesizes LLM text back into human-like audio using models of your choice (Deepgram, Cartesia, ElevenLabs, OpenAI).</li>
					<li><strong>Orchestrator:</strong> Manages conversational context, interruption handling, tool-calling (APIs), and latency mitigation.</li>
				</ol>

				<h2>Next Steps</h2>
				<p>Ready to get your first voice agent running? Head over to the quickstart guide to clone the repository and initialize the docker containers.</p>
				
				<div class="code-block">
<pre><code>git clone https://github.com/your-org/open-bolna.git
cd open-bolna
docker-compose up -d</code></pre>
				</div>
			</section>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>